author: Zach Montellaro
title: Wisconsin’s coronavirus election results set to kick off more lawsuits
description: State Democrats said early Monday that "every legal option is on the table" regarding voting access during the April 7 election.
content: But the state Supreme Court, which currently has a 5-2 conservative margin, ultimately ruled that Evers did not have the authority to postpone the election after the legislature challenged his order. That meant in-person voting happened as planned, even thoug… [+2092 chars]
